2.	What do the following lines of code output? Why do they give a different answer?
print(2 / 3)		0.6666666666666666(output) 	quotient: / 
print(2 // 3)		0(output) 				integer quotient: //
quotient(/) gives you an exact answer including decimal points while integer quotient(//) rounds up the answer to the nearest number


